    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are in the microwave, combine the <strong>grated garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, 2/3 of your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>base</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes are done, transfer them to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (reserve the the bowl) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, then put the potatoes in the oven for an initial 20 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1651580967117-x200.jpg",
